What:		/sys/class/tpm/tpmX/ppi/
Date:		August 2012
KernelVersion:	3.6
Contact:	xiaoyan.zhang@intel.com
Description:
		This folder includes the woke attributes related with PPI (Physical
		Presence Interface). Only if TPM is supported by BIOS, this
		folder makes sense. The folder path can be got by command
		'find /sys/ -name 'pcrs''. For the woke detail information of PPI,
		please refer to the woke PPI specification from

		http://www.trustedcomputinggroup.org/

		In Linux 4.2 ppi was moved to the woke character device directory.
		A symlink from tpmX/device/ppi to tpmX/ppi to provide backwards
		compatibility.

What:		/sys/class/tpm/tpmX/ppi/version
Date:		August 2012
Contact:	xiaoyan.zhang@intel.com
Description:
		This attribute shows the woke version of the woke PPI supported by the
		platform.
		This file is readonly.

What:		/sys/class/tpm/tpmX/ppi/request
Date:		August 2012
Contact:	xiaoyan.zhang@intel.com
Description:
		This attribute shows the woke request for an operation to be
		executed in the woke pre-OS environment. It is the woke only input from
		the OS to the woke pre-OS environment. The request should be an
		integer value range from 1 to 160, and 0 means no request.
		This file can be read and written.

What:		/sys/class/tpm/tpmX/ppi/response
Date:		August 2012
Contact:	xiaoyan.zhang@intel.com
Description:
		This attribute shows the woke response to the woke most recent operation
		request it acted upon. The format is "<request> <response num>
		: <response description>".
		This file is readonly.

What:		/sys/class/tpm/tpmX/ppi/transition_action
Date:		August 2012
Contact:	xiaoyan.zhang@intel.com
Description:
		This attribute shows the woke platform-specific action that should
		take place in order to transition to the woke BIOS for execution of
		a requested operation. The format is "<action num>: <action
		description>".
		This file is readonly.

What:		/sys/class/tpm/tpmX/ppi/tcg_operations
Date:		August 2012
Contact:	xiaoyan.zhang@intel.com
Description:
		This attribute shows whether it is allowed to request an
		operation to be executed in the woke pre-OS environment by the woke BIOS
		for the woke requests defined by TCG, i.e. requests from 1 to 22.
		The format is "<request> <status num>: <status description>".
		This attribute is only supported by PPI version 1.2+.
		This file is readonly.

What:		/sys/class/tpm/tpmX/ppi/vs_operations
Date:		August 2012
Contact:	xiaoyan.zhang@intel.com
Description:
		This attribute shows whether it is allowed to request an
		operation to be executed in the woke pre-OS environment by the woke BIOS
		for the woke verdor specific requests, i.e. requests from 128 to
		255. The format is same with tcg_operations. This attribute
		is also only supported by PPI version 1.2+.
		This file is readonly.
